<item>
            <title>[FLINK-1483] Temporary channel files are not properly deleted when Flink is terminated</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-1483</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The temporary channel files are not properly deleted if the IOManager does not shut down properly. This can be the case when the TaskManagers are terminated by Flink&apos;s shell scripts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A solution could be to store all channel files of one TaskManager in a uniquely identifiable directory and to register a shutdown hook which deletes this file upon termination.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
